        <div class="verdict">✓ Updated April 2026</div>

        <p>Estimating is where construction projects are won or lost. Bid too high and you lose the job. Bid too low and you lose money. The right estimating software helps you price accurately, present professionally, and win more of the jobs you actually want.</p>

        <p>The challenge: "estimating software" means different things depending on your trade and project type. A custom homebuilder estimating a $800K renovation has completely different needs than a commercial GC bidding a $10M office tenant improvement.</p>

        <h2>Types of estimating software</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>All-in-one PM platforms with built-in estimating</strong> — Buildertrend, JobTread, Procore. Estimating is one module within a larger system.</li>
          <li><strong>Standalone estimating tools</strong> — PlanSwift, Bluebeam, ProEst. Purpose-built for takeoff and cost assembly.</li>
          <li><strong>Specialty estimating</strong> — Tools built for specific trades (electrical, mechanical, roofing).</li>
        </ul>

